Implement Phase 2 interaction polish for the IT Asset Management System at `/Users/admin/it-asset/`.

## 2A — Toast Notification System

Create a lightweight toast system. Do NOT install any npm packages. Build it with React context + portal.

### Create `components/ui/toast.tsx` (single file, self-contained):

```tsx
"use client"

import { createContext, useContext, useState, useCallback, type ReactNode } from "react"
import { createPortal } from "react-dom"
import { X } from "lucide-react"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

interface Toast {
  id: string
  title: string
  description?: string
  variant: "default" | "destructive" | "success"
}

interface ToastContextValue {
  toast: (t: Omit<Toast, "id">) => void
}

const ToastContext = createContext<ToastContextValue | null>(null)

export function useToast() {
  const ctx = useContext(ToastContext)
  if (!ctx) throw new Error("useToast must be used within ToastProvider")
  return ctx
}

export function ToastProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  const [toasts, setToasts] = useState<Toast[]>([])

  const addToast = useCallback((t: Omit<Toast, "id">) => {
    const id = Math.random().toString(36).slice(2)
    setToasts((prev) => [...prev, { ...t, id }])
    setTimeout(() => {
      setToasts((prev) => prev.filter((x) => x.id !== id))
    }, 5000)
  }, [])

  const dismiss = useCallback((id: string) => {
    setToasts((prev) => prev.filter((x) => x.id !== id))
  }, [])

  const variantStyles: Record<Toast["variant"], string> = {
    default: "border-border bg-background",
    destructive: "border-destructive/30 bg-destructive/10 text-destructive",
    success: "border-status-green/30 bg-status-green/10 text-status-green",
  }

  return (
    <ToastContext.Provider value={{ toast: addToast }}>
      {children}
      {typeof window !== "undefined" &&
        createPortal(
          <div className="fixed bottom-4 right-4 z-50 flex flex-col gap-2 max-w-sm w-full pointer-events-none">
            {toasts.map((t) => (
              <div
                key={t.id}
                className={cn(
                  "pointer-events-auto rounded-lg border p-4 shadow-lg animate-[page-in_0.2s_ease-out]",
                  variantStyles[t.variant]
                )}
              >
                <div className="flex items-start justify-between gap-2">
                  <div className="space-y-1">
                    <p className="text-sm font-medium">{t.title}</p>
                    {t.description && <p className="text-sm opacity-80">{t.description}</p>}
                  </div>
                  <button onClick={() => dismiss(t.id)} className="shrink-0 rounded-md p-1 hover:bg-muted">
                    <X className="size-4" />
                  </button>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>,
          document.body
        )}
    </ToastContext.Provider>
  )
}
```

### Integrate ToastProvider in `app/layout.tsx`

Read the file first. Import `ToastProvider` from `@/components/ui/toast` and wrap `{children}` with `<ToastProvider>`. The layout already has `<AuthProvider>` wrapping — add ToastProvider inside AuthProvider.

### Replace inline error banners with toast in key pages

For these 3 key pages, replace the inline `submitError`/`error` state display with toast notifications:

**`app/login/page.tsx`:**
- On login error (catch block ~line 78-80): replace `setError(message)` with toast. Keep the error state for form-level display (the `error !== null && <div>...</div>` block at the bottom) — don't change the visual, just add `toast({ title: "登录失败", description: message, variant: "destructive" })` in addition.

**`app/apply/page.tsx`:**
- On submit error: add `toast({ title: "提交失败", description: err.message, variant: "destructive" })` 
- On submit success: after `router.push(...)`, you can't show toast (page navigates away). Skip.
- Keep the existing error display as is, just add the toast.

**`app/it/inbound/page.tsx`:**
- On success: replace the green success banner div at the bottom with a toast: `toast({ title: "入库成功", variant: "success" })`. Remove the `success` state variable and the green banner JSX.

For each page you modify:
1. Read the file first
2. Import `useToast` from `@/components/ui/toast`
3. Add `const { toast } = useToast()` inside the component
4. Add toast calls in catch/success blocks

## 2D — Header Scroll Shadow

### Modify `components/layout/header.tsx`

Read the file first. Add a scroll shadow effect:
1. Add state: `const [scrolled, setScrolled] = useState(false)`
2. Add a `useEffect` that sets up an IntersectionObserver or listens for scroll on the main content area
3. Since the header is inside a layout with ScrollArea, use a simpler approach: add an event listener on the scroll container

Actually, simplest approach for the header scroll shadow: use the `cn` utility to conditionally add a shadow class:

```tsx
const [scrolled, setScrolled] = useState(false)

useEffect(() => {
  // Find the scroll container (the ScrollArea viewport)
  const viewport = document.querySelector('[data-slot="scroll-area-viewport"]')
  if (!viewport) return
  const handleScroll = () => setScrolled(viewport.scrollTop > 0)
  viewport.addEventListener("scroll", handleScroll, { passive: true })
  return () => viewport.removeEventListener("scroll", handleScroll)
}, [])
```

Then on the header element, add: `className={cn("...", scrolled && "shadow-sm")}`  (or `border-b-0 shadow-sm border-b border-transparent` when not scrolled, and a visible border/shadow when scrolled)

Actually, keep it simple: just add `transition-shadow` and conditionally apply `shadow-sm` based on scroll position.

## Verification

After all edits, run `npx tsc --noEmit` to verify TypeScript compiles cleanly.

